ttps://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/every-winter-canadian-rivers-produce-giant-spinning-circles-of-ice-scientists-now-know-why/articleshow/132362415.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-13T16:00:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132362622,imgsize-213002.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[This AI founder walked away from a $300,000 life in San Francisco: 'No money could make me stay here']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132361454.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Koby Conrad, founder of AI sobriety companion Sunflower, relocated to Buenos Aires. He found a better environment for building a family and his company. Conrad enjoys the city's culture, food, and significantly lower living costs. He feels more focused and productive away from San Francisco's tech-centric atmosphere. The move supports his desire to balance ambitious work with raising a family.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/this-ai-founder-walked-away-from-a-300000-life-in-san-francisco-no-money-could-make-me-stay-here/articleshow/132361454.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/this-ai-founder-walked-away-from-a-300000-life-in-san-francisco-no-money-could-make-me-stay-here/articleshow/132361454.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-13T15:30:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132361662,imgsize-123036.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[18 ancient Egyptian tombs found with golden tongues]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132362227.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Recently, a remarkable discovery was made with the unearthing of eighteen ancient Egyptian tombs near Marina el-Alamein. Among the intriguing artifacts found were sealed stone slabs, an impressive granite coffin, and dozens of gold tongues strategically placed in the mouths of mummies to assist them in speaking in the afterlife. Additionally, an intricately designed offering altar and a statue of Aphrodite were also uncovered, shedding light on ancient burial practices.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/18-ancient-egyptian-tombs-found-along-the-mediterranean-coast-with-dozens-of-gold-tongues-meant-for-the-afterlife/articleshow/132362227.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/18-ancient-egyptian-tombs-found-along-the-mediterranean-coast-with-dozens-of-gold-tongues-meant-for-the-afterlife/articleshow/132362227.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-13T14:55:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132362351,imgsize-779886.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why Prince George wore suit at Wimbledon, even in the heat]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132359734.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Prince George and Prince William attended the Wimbledon men's final in formal attire. They adhered to the Royal Box dress code, which mandates suits and ties. Despite the heat, this strict protocol was followed by the royal attendees. Children are rarely permitted in the exclusive Royal Box seating area. However, Prince George and Princess Charlotte were exceptions to this unwritten rule.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/why-did-prince-william-and-princess-of-wales-kate-middleton-catherines-son-prince-george-suit-to-wimbledon-2026/articleshow/132359734.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/uk/why-did-prince-william-and-princess-of-wales-kate-middleton-catherines-son-prince-george-suit-to-wimbledon-2026/articleshow/132359734.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-13T13:19:53+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132360321,imgsize-623922.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[In 1906, one wrong turn sent the SS Valencia into the Pacific's “Graveyard of the Pacific”, where more than 100 people died]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132361937.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1906-one-wrong-turn-sent-the-ss-valencia-into-the-pacifics-graveyard-of-the-pacific-where-more-than-100-people-died/articleshow/132361937.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/in-1906-one-wrong-turn-sent-the-ss-valencia-into-the-pacifics-graveyard-of-the-pacific-where-more-than-100-people-died/articleshow/132361937.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-13T15:15:00+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132362224,imgsize-195897.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[65-year-old grandfather attacked by a Yellowstone bison was cracking jokes despite breaking multiple bones]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132361635.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/65-year-old-grandfather-attacked-by-a-yellowstone-bison-was-cracking-jokes-despite-breaking-m